-- Polecat PR Review — review an external PR and decide merge/reject/revise.
-- Self-cleaning model: review, submit findings, gt done, gone.

## polecat-review-pr

  input param.pr_url : str required
  input param.issue : str required
  input param.rig : str required

  # load-context : llm
    system>
      You are a polecat reviewing an external PR. Self-cleaning model:
      review, submit findings, run gt done, you cease to exist.
    user>
      Prime environment and understand the PR:
      ```bash
      gt prime
      bd prime
      gt hook
      bd show {{param.issue}}
      gh pr view {{param.pr_url}} --json title,body,author,files,commits
      gh pr diff {{param.pr_url}}
      gh pr checks {{param.pr_url}}
      gh pr view {{param.pr_url}} --json mergeable,reviewDecision
      ```
      Understand purpose, scope, and CI status.
    accept>
      PR purpose and scope understood.
  #/

  # review-code : llm
    - load-context
    system>
      You are reviewing code changes. Be thorough and actionable.
    user>
      Review the diff systematically:
      ```bash
      gh pr diff {{param.pr_url}}
      ```
      Check for: correctness, security, style, tests, docs, scope creep.
      For each file, assess consistency with existing patterns.
      Categorize issues: blocking (must fix), suggestions, questions.
    format> findings
      { blocking: [str], suggestions: [str], questions: [str] }
  #/

  # check-tests : llm
    - review-code
    system>
      You are verifying CI and test coverage for a PR.
    user>
      ```bash
      gh pr checks {{param.pr_url}}
      ```
      Verify: CI passes, new tests for new functionality, edge case coverage,
      test readability. Missing tests for new code is a blocking issue.
    format> test_status
      { ci_pass: boolean, has_new_tests: boolean, missing_tests: [str] }
  #/

  # make-decision : decision
    - check-tests
    system>
      You are a PR reviewer making a final decision.
      Decision matrix: clean code + tests pass = APPROVE.
      Minor issues = REQUEST_CHANGES with specifics.
      Major issues = REQUEST_CHANGES with explanation.
      Unclear requirements = NEEDS_DISCUSSION (mail Witness).
      Security concern = BLOCK (mail Witness immediately).
    user>
      Based on review findings and test status, decide:
      APPROVE, REQUEST_CHANGES, NEEDS_DISCUSSION, or BLOCK.
      If NEEDS_DISCUSSION or BLOCK, mail the witness:
      ```bash
      gt mail send {{param.rig}}/witness -s "PR review: <decision>" -m "PR: {{param.pr_url}}
      Issue: {{param.issue}}
      Detail: <rationale>"
      ```
    format> verdict
      { decision: str, rationale: str, blocking_count: number }

    ```oracle
    json_parse(output);
    assert output.decision in ["APPROVE", "REQUEST_CHANGES", "NEEDS_DISCUSSION", "BLOCK"];
    ```
  #/

  # submit-review : script
    - make-decision
    ```bash
    case "{{make-decision.decision}}" in
      APPROVE)
        gh pr review {{param.pr_url}} --approve --body "{{make-decision.rationale}}"
        ;;
      REQUEST_CHANGES)
        gh pr review {{param.pr_url}} --request-changes --body "{{make-decision.rationale}}"
        ;;
      *)
        gh pr review {{param.pr_url}} --comment --body "{{make-decision.rationale}}"
        ;;
    esac
    echo "review_submitted"
    ```

    ```oracle
    assert output contains "review_submitted";
    ```
  #/

  # file-followups : llm
    - submit-review
    system>
      You are filing beads for followup work discovered during review.
    user>
      For issues outside PR scope:
      ```bash
      bd create --type=bug --title="Found during PR review: <desc>" \
        --description="Discovered reviewing {{param.pr_url}}. <details>"
      ```
      For improvements suggested but not required:
      ```bash
      bd create --type=task --title="Improvement: <desc>" \
        --description="Suggested during review of {{param.pr_url}}. <details>"
      ```
      Update the tracking issue:
      ```bash
      bd update {{param.issue}} --notes "Review complete. Decision: {{make-decision.decision}}"
      bd sync
      ```
    accept>
      All followups filed and synced.
  #/

  # complete-and-exit : script
    - file-followups
    ```bash
    bd sync
    gt done
    echo "done"
    ```
  #/

  squash> trigger: on_complete template: work include_metrics: true

##/
